Program: The Documentary
Title: Central Park Calling
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csxgwb
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 1 Aug 2018
Is being disagreeable a good thing? Is how we identify becoming more complex? And what is the one thing conservative Republicans are wishing President Trump would do next? They are all topics that were under discussion at this year’s OZY Fest – a summer festival of ideas, music, comedy and food held in New York’s Central Park. This is the best of the two day fest with Lizzie O’Leary. (Photo Credit: Bryony Shearmur) Show less